{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the human motions collected from the body-fixed sensors play important roles in the daily physical activity validation.",
    "Conventionally, ambulatory computations for physical activities are executed by considering motion sensors like an actometer, accelerometers fixed in the waist, ankle, or wrist, and pedometers 22.",
    "Yet, these procedures did not offer essential information for the medical professionals about the activity type.",
    "Hence, professionals designed novel mechanisms to detect the individual's activities, but these techniques face more difficulties as they are attached to multiple sites.Medical professionals handling the disabled, aged, bedridden, and injured persons lack in using the computers and technologies 23.",
    "Therefore, to offer a better experience to users, HCI is widely introduced in the medical field to identify the motions and intentions of the people who provide better support 24."
  ]
}